{
  "stem": "19690.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "We learned-- this was in the Italian part of Switzerland-- I had to learn German again because I'd forgotten my German learning French.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "So we were being taught in French, essentially, but we were also being told, refresh your other languages.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "While we were there, people would come and interview us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And one of the things that happened was that I mentioned this family [NON-ENGLISH] in [NON-ENGLISH] as having been our contact.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And I immediately wrote to them, here I am, because I wanted to know where my cousin, Lizel, was, who also was supposed to contact them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Well, she was still in France.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "But when the committee found out that I had these people there, they suggested I move in with them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Well, they are older people, they have grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "They were in no shape to take care of this 14-year-old or 13-year-old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "So they found a Mrs.-- another Mrs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "Bloch, who was in charge of the committee, in Winterthur.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And this lady found a family who had a two and a half year old little boy who was willing to take on an older boy, feeling that I would be a help rather than a hindrance.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And on a trial basis I would put-- was put with these people for a month.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "Their name was Jacob-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] --and Helen Neff.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "They lived on [NON-ENGLISH] 49 in Winterthur, near Zurich.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] They became and still are my second family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "They're still alive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "I'm in contact with them always.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "We-- I lived with them for a month, and unknownst to me until 1979, when we went to visit them, did I find out that after months, they said yes, they would keep me indefinitely and they did not want any money for it.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
